9. <!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
<style>
table {
  border-collapse: collapse;
  width: 100%;
}

th, td {
  padding: 2px;
  text-align: left;
  border-bottom: 2px solid #ddd;
}

tr:hover {background-color: goldenrod;}
</style>
</head>
<body>

<h2>Hoverable Table</h2>

<p>Move the mouse over the table rows to see the effect.</p>

<table>
  <tr>
    <th>First Name</th>
    <th>Last Name</th>
    <th>Points</th>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>Peter</td>
    <td>Griffin</td>
    <td>$50</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>Louis</td>
    <td>Shaha</td>
    <td>$150</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>Hervy</td>
    <td>Jhonson</td>
    <td>$25000</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>Cleveland</td>
    <td>Hridoy</td>
    <td>$450</td>
  </tr>
</table>

</body>
</html>

10. <!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
<style> 
input[type=text] {
  width: 100%;
  padding: 12px 20px;
  margin: 8px 0;
  box-sizing: border-box;
  border: 1px solid #666;
  outline: none;
}

input[type=text]:focus {
  background-color: lightblue;
}
</style>
</head>
<body>

<h2>Input fields with color on :focus</h2>

<p>Here, the input field gets a color when it gets focus (clicked on):</p>

<form>
  <label for="fname">First Name</label>
  <input type="text" id="fname" name="fname" value="Hridoy">
  <label for="lname">Last Name</label>
  <input type="text" id="lname" name="lname" value="Shaha">
</form>

</body>
</html>

